.TH UPGRADE-DEBIAN 1 "December 2025" "distup 1.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
upgrade-debian \- upgrade Debian to stable, testing, or sid
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B upgrade-debian
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fBstable\fR|\fBtesting\fR|\fBsid\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B upgrade-debian
upgrades Debian systems to stable, testing, or sid/unstable branches.
It handles repository configuration, package updates, and full system upgrade.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
Show what would be done without making any changes.
.TP
.B \-\-version\fR, \fB\-V
Show version information.
.TP
.B \-\-help\fR, \fB\-h
Show help message.
.SH MODES
.TP
.B stable
Current stable release. Recommended for production systems.
.TP
.B testing
Testing branch with newer packages. May have occasional bugs.
.TP
.B sid
Unstable/sid branch. Rolling release with latest packages.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/apt/sources.list
Repository configuration (backed up before modification).
.TP
.I /var/log/upgrade-debian-*.log
Log file containing detailed upgrade output.
